The KwaZulu-Natal Department of Health has announced a mass testing and screening programme in all 11 provincial districts. The programme was rolled out today (Monday, 13 April) and will continue until 17 April. The districts include Amajuba, Harry Gwala, Ilembe, King Cetshwayo, eThekwini, Ugu, Umgungundlovu, uMkhanyakude, uMzinyathi, uThukela and Zululand. Below please find a link to download the schedule for the various areas in Kwa-Zulu Natal. Click on the link to download.